## Skills

The following skills are installed in `~/.claude/skills/`:

### SDD Workflow
- `sdd-orchestrator` — **Entry point**: run `/sdd-new`, `/sdd-ff`, or `/sdd-continue` to start
- `sdd-init` — Initialize SDD context in a project
- `sdd-explore` — Investigate ideas before committing to a change
- `sdd-propose` — Create a change proposal with intent, scope, and approach
- `sdd-spec` — Write specifications with Given/When/Then scenarios
- `sdd-design` — Write technical design document with architecture decisions
- `sdd-tasks` — Break down a change into a numbered implementation checklist
- `sdd-apply` — Implement tasks from the change following specs and design
- `sdd-verify` — Validate that implementation matches specs, design, and tasks
- `sdd-archive` — Archive a completed change and sync delta specs
- `sdd-onboard` — Guided end-to-end walkthrough of the full SDD workflow

### Utilities
- `engram:memory` — Persistent memory protocol (ALWAYS ACTIVE)
- `branch-pr` — PR creation workflow following issue-first enforcement
- `issue-creation` — GitHub issue creation workflow
- `judgment-day` — Parallel adversarial review: two blind judge sub-agents
- `skill-creator` — Create new AI agent skills following the Agent Skills spec
- `skill-registry` — Create or update the skill registry for the current project

### Domain
- `zoho-deluge` — Zoho Deluge coding standard: statement optimization, security, scalability

